# Commit workflow

Before creating any git commit in KeenAI:

1. Run `pnpm lint` and fix all errors (use `pnpm lint:fix` when safe).
2. Only commit if lint passes with exit code 0.
3. Do not skip hooks (`--no-verify`) unless the user explicitly requests it.
4. Use [Conventional Commits](https://www.conventionalcommits.org/) (`feat:`, `fix:`, `docs:`, etc.) — enforced by the commit-msg hook.
5. For Phase 4 memory iterations ([08-ROADMAP-TODO.md](../docs/08-ROADMAP-TODO.md) KM-*): also run `pnpm typecheck` and `pnpm test` before commit; push with `git push` after each iteration unless the user says otherwise.

The repo also installs a **pre-commit hook** (`.githooks/pre-commit`) via `pnpm install` that runs `pnpm lint` automatically for local commits.
